        "text": "May virtual meetup • <https:\/\/time.is\/1800_27_MAY_2026_in_UTC?Virtual_Meetup|Wed May 27 at 18:00 UTC> • <https:\/\/luma.com\/15v0fpx1|RSVP>\n\nI was always afraid this would happen. It's been — what — 20 years? Longer? Of waiting. Wondering. Ignoring.\n\nFeeling too afraid to feel. Wanting it to be something. It not.\n\nWell no longer!\n\nThis week, we'll have demos ~from at least two people. Yeah, that's right, we don't have a third person to demo something yet. I guess this is the quiet time of year. If you wanna demo something, DM me and say so! Would love to have you.~ TOO LATE SUCKERS! We're now _packed_ with demos. Everyone rules.\n\n• Jasmine Otto has an update to a project she demoed before called Multiplayer Bitsy, which is a cute lil env for making games, used in education. This is legit authentic use stuff, y'all'll love it.\n• Ivan Lugo reached out with a cool web-based IDE experiment he's been tinkering on.\n• Luke Stanley has a… well, heck, I'm just gonna copy-paste what he said cuz it rules: \"a 2D visual language topic map ZUI with a tricky no-overlap but high semantic spatial fidelity condition (from highly dimensional semantic embeddings). It's an annoyingly thorny problem that people will laugh at as being hard in no time at all though. (But that's probably true of most things.)\"\nCool.",
